  "texts": [
    "2-2 Pachner moves in the dual triangulation).",
    "In particular, one can perform local fusion of TDLs using the F-moves.",
    "The F-symbols obey nontrivial algebraic constraints known as pentagon equations, coming from the consistency condition under consecutive changes of basis in the five-point junction vector space (which can be derived from the isotopy invariance of the associated TDL configuration [10]).",
    "Unsurprisingly the pentagon equations are direct analogs of the cocycle conditions for group cohomology H 3 (G, U(1)) that classifies anomalies for discrete group symmetry.",
    "Once the pentagon equations are solved, there are no further independent consistency conditions on the F-symbols, as a consequence of the Mac Lane coherence theorem [11]."
  ]
